Reamaning to do are below questions------

====================================



1. Manual Operations & Manipulations

Reverse an integer array in place (without extra array).

Rotate an array to the right by k positions.

Rotate an array to the left by k positions.

Remove all occurrences of a given element from the array and print the resulting array.

Replace all occurrences of one number with another number.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Counting & Summarizing

Count how many elements are greater than a given number.

Find the second largest element in an array.

Calculate sum of elements at even indices and odd indices separately.

Find the average of elements in an array.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


3. Array Utility Practice (Manual + API)

Manually copy the first N elements of one array into a new array (without Arrays.copyOf()).

Manually fill an array with a specific value (without using Arrays.fill()).

Manually compare two arrays element by element (without Arrays.equals()).

Convert a char[] array to a String explicitly (new String(charArray)).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. Arrays with Methods

Write a method to concatenate two integer arrays and return the combined array.

Write a method that takes two arrays and prints the common elements.

Write a method to find and return the index of the maximum element in an array.

Write a method to check if an array is sorted in ascending order.


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5. Edge Cases & Validation

Handle and print appropriate messages for empty arrays or null arrays in all your methods.

Take input from user for array size and elements, then print only elements greater than a user-entered threshold.

